<p> As you can see, there is a lot of computation with this test. But the good news is that technology can help us out. We will be creating a matrix in the calculator so it can compute the expected values for us. </p>
<p> Find the MATRIX above the [<m>x^{-1}</m>] button. </p>
<p>Press [2nd] [<m>x^{-1}</m>] for the Matrix, use the arrow to the right twice for the EDIT menu, we are going to select matrix  <term>1: A </term> and press [ENTER]. </p>
<p>We need to identify the size of the matrix, input 3 rows (across/horizontal) x 3 columns (down/vertical) and then input the observed data by hitting [ENTER] after each entry. </p>
