<p><term> Social Media Usage</term></p> 
<p>
      A marketing researcher wants to determine whether the type of social media
      platform most often used is independent of age group. A random sample of
      <m>230</m> adults is classified by age group and by the social media
      platform they report using most often.
    </p>
    <table>
      <title>Most-Used Social Media Platform by Age Group</title>
      <tabular>
        <row>
          <cell>Age Group</cell>
          <cell>Facebook</cell>
          <cell>Instagram</cell>
          <cell>TikTok</cell>
          <cell>WhatsApp</cell>
          <cell>YouTube</cell>
          <cell>Total</cell>
        </row>
        <row><cell>Under 30</cell><cell>12</cell><cell>22</cell><cell>18</cell><cell>8</cell><cell>10</cell><cell>70</cell></row>
        <row><cell>30--50</cell><cell>20</cell><cell>16</cell><cell>9</cell><cell>15</cell><cell>20</cell><cell>80</cell></row>
        <row><cell>Over 50</cell><cell>34</cell><cell>8</cell><cell>3</cell><cell>12</cell><cell>23</cell><cell>80</cell></row>
        <row><cell>Total</cell><cell>66</cell><cell>46</cell><cell>30</cell><cell>35</cell><cell>53</cell><cell>230</cell></row>
      </tabular>
    </table>
    <p>
      At the <m>0.05</m> significance level, test whether most-used social media
      platform is associated with age group.
    </p>

<exercise xml:id="ex-chisquare-independence-social-media">
<title> Social Media Usage</title>
  <statement>
<p> Find</p>
  </statement>
  <solution> <title>Hypotheses</title>
      <p>
      This is a chi-square test of independence. A random sample was taken and at least 5 in almost every cell.
    </p>
    <p> The hypotheses are </p>
     <p> <m>H_0:</m> social media platform most often used and age group are independent. </p>
    <p> <m>H_a:</m> social media platform most often used and age group are dependent.
    </p>
</solution>
<solution> <title> Expected Values</title>
    <p>
      The expected count for each cell is found by using
      <m>
        E=\dfrac{(\text{row total})(\text{column total})}{\text{grand total}}.
      </m>
    </p>
    <p>
      For example, the expected count for adults under <m>30</m> who most often
      use Facebook is
      <m>
        E=\dfrac{(70)(66)}{230}\approx 20.09.
      </m>
    </p>
    <table>
      <title>Expected Counts</title>
      <tabular>
        <row>
          <cell>Age Group</cell>
          <cell>Facebook</cell>
          <cell>Instagram</cell>
          <cell>TikTok</cell>
          <cell>WhatsApp</cell>
          <cell>YouTube</cell>
        </row>
        <row><cell>Under 30</cell><cell><m>20.09</m></cell><cell><m>14.00</m></cell><cell><m>9.13</m></cell><cell><m>10.65</m></cell><cell><m>16.13</m></cell></row>
        <row><cell>30--50</cell><cell><m>22.96</m></cell><cell><m>16.00</m></cell><cell><m>10.43</m></cell><cell><m>12.17</m></cell><cell><m>18.43</m></cell></row>
        <row><cell>Over 50</cell><cell><m>22.96</m></cell><cell><m>16.00</m></cell><cell><m>10.43</m></cell><cell><m>12.17</m></cell><cell><m>18.43</m></cell></row>
      </tabular>
    </table>
  </solution>
<solution> <title> Test Statistic</title>
    <p>
      Using all cells, the test statistic is
      <m>
        \chi^2=\sum \frac{(O-E)^2}{E}\approx 36.54
      </m>
    </p>
    <p>
      The degrees of freedom are
      <m>
        (r-1)(c-1)=(3-1)(5-1)=8.
      </m>
    </p>
    <p>
      Using a chi-square distribution with <m>8</m> degrees of freedom, the
      <m>p</m>-value is <m>p=0.000014</m>.
    </p>
    <figure xml:id="ChiSquareSocials">
            <caption>Chi-square test for social media</caption>
            <image source="ChiSocial.png" width="80%">
                <shortdescription>select option C for chi-square test. Test value =36.54 and p=0.000014</shortdescription>
            </image>
        </figure> 

</solution>
<solution> <title> Conclusion</title>
    <p> Since <m>p \lt 0.05</m>, we reject <m>H_0</m>.
    </p>
    <p>
      There is sufficient evidence at the 0.05 significance level to
      conclude that most-used social media platform is associated with age group.
    </p>
    <p>
      In context, the pattern of platform use differs across the three age
      groups. Younger adults are more likely to report Instagram and TikTok as
      their most-used platforms, while older adults are more likely to report
      Facebook and YouTube.
    </p>
  </solution>
</exercise> 



</subsection>

</section> 
